<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Written evidence submitted by Prof</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence submitted by the School of</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> Law, University of Edinburgh (GHS0017)</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">SCRIPT Centre for IT and IP Law is an interdisciplinary research centre at the School of Law of the University of Edinburgh. Initially funded by the AHRC, it carries out research in the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">intersection </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> between law, science and technology. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Since its inception</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, it organises </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> several “foresight fora” that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">try</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> to anticipate emerging legal issues in the fields of internet, IP and medical law. Its current director is Prof Burkhard Schafer, who also authored this response.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">In relation to autonomous vehicles and in</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">telligent transport infrastructure:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">What are (or were) the policy challenges presented by this technology? How have these challenges been identified?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">How prepared is (or was) the Government to react to challenges presented by this techn</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">ology? How effective was this reaction?</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">1) </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">Summary:</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The legal and regulatory implications of autonomous vehicles are complex, multifaceted and range across a variety of legal fields. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Need for regulatory reform has been identified with varying degrees of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">urgency – some reform needed right now to enable the development</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and testing </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> of the technology</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, other issues </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> require</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> medium to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">  long term strategies</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to enable production and uptake</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> also with </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">a view </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> to</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> amend </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> international </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">treaties and coordinate inter</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">national </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">standards</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Several legal issues will be outside the (full) control of th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">e</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> UK government, raising international or devolved issues.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The legal </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">reform </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">debate is most advanced in the US with regards to road traffic law/licensing, and in continental </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Europe with regards to liability regimes. The UK debate is comparatively </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">muted</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> (but at a similar level to that in Japan)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Readiness for reform is difficult to gauge.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">T</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">his “wait and see” approach may well have beneficial aspects</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> as some of the discussion raises the danger of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">unnecessarily </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">radical</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> reform caused by the perceived, rather  than actual, novelty of the technologies, with limited understanding of their</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> capabilities and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> limitations.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Court –led </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">“Incrementalism” might su</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">it the common law approach to regulation better, but can </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">cause</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> tensions within the EU. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">I</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">n some areas </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">however, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">action will be needed soon. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">In particular if we want cars that are “law abiding by design”, computer friendly clarification of road traffic law </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">are needed.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> HORIZON project has had so far</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> limited impact on that debate – its </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">outcomes</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">are potentially useful</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, but underused, for legal analysis. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Information flow in the opposite direction, contribution </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">by</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">legal academics</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> in the identification of fut</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ure regulatory issues</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, and development of possible reform proposals, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">seems to be ver</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">y limited.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">I</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">nternational studies</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and EU initiatives</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> remain the main point of reference – problematic due to the national particularities of legal systems that make transfer</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> of ideas in law more difficult than in the sciences.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">2) </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">Legal issues </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">and policy challenges </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">of autonomous vehicles</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps"> (A</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">V</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">s)</span></p><ol type="A" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 32.47pt; padding-left:3.53pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">General considerations</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The legal challenges created by autonomous cars are many and multifaceted</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, ranging from </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">obvious issues such as</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">updating the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Road Traffic Act and Hig</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">hway Code to the law of delict/tort</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, insurance law, criminal law, data protection law, RIPA, intellectual property law, competition law, contract law, disability law, criminal and civil procedural law and the law of ev</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">idence, some of which involving international laws and treaties.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Before attempting</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> to give a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">list, it is helpful to consider a few </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">more abstract </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">parameters to structure these: </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Legal issues of autonomous </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">vehicles </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> can be caused by </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Antiquated laws preventing unintentionally the testing, development </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">or uptake of</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> ACs</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. This creates </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">possible </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">need to legislate </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">for</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> technology</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The technology can create new risks, including new forms of crime, that are not adequately covered by existing</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> laws – the need for regulation </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">of</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> technology.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">is also includes debates on whether the mere perception of risk, e.g. by the wide</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">r</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> population or by insurance companies, merits to create legal reassurances </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">that are not objectively justified.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Emerging legal</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> issues of AVs can be</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Specific to the car and the car industry (example </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">e.g. the definition of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> “fitness to  drive”)</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Generic  issues created by autonomous technologies (example: applicability of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">legal </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">terms such as</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">“reasonable forseability”, “consent” or </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">“malicious intent” to machines)</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Imported from other technological fields, e.g emerging legal issues of internet law that affect the communication of the car with a base station (example: possible data retention duties for car manufacturers/sellers)</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">As alwa</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ys, legal issues can arise on the subnational (devolved), national and international including EU) level. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">From a UK perspective, this means that future pressures on the UK legal system  can be caused by</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Developments in the technology</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and the needs of the U</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">K car manufacturers</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Individual events that create pressure to act (</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">e.g. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">an accident with fatalities)</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Future reactions of international bodies and organisations to these developments</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> over which the UK has some, but no full control (e.g.  changes to the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Gen</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">eva </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> Convention; EU initiatives to prevent market fragmentation)</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Manufacturing  developments in other countries that affect </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> UK law </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">through the legal framework of the WTO (e.g. US car makers arguing that UK safety rules are a trade barrier</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, or that the abs</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ence of a suitable legal framework is inherently a protectionist measure)</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Finally, the degree of legal changes </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">that is </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">needed will obviously depend </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">o</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">n the degree of autonomy and the fun</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ctionality embedded in the car – ranging from merely assistive technolo</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">gies to self-driving cars with a human driver </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">“in the loop” to the vision of the fully automated car </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">that like a chauffeur drops </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">its owner </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> off at </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">his </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> destination and then drives itself home. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Legal issues can combine </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">issues across </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">all of the above parameters, creating a large number of  very heterogeneous </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">problems</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, that make considerable demands on the expertise needed to address them. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">To give some impression of the diversity of the issues that can come up, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">3</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> examples</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, from opposing</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> ends of the spectrum</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, all of which with uncertain legal answers and the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">potential</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> need for law reform.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">1)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">A challenge at the WTO that UK regulation on the safety standards for </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">AVs </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">are unreasonable given the developments in technology and therefore discrim</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">inate</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> against US manufacturers</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">2) A driver is accused of murdering his wife with his car. The main evidence comes from 2 on</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> board sensors of the car, which operate independently, but whose inputs are processed by the same </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">central </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">computer</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> unit on the ca</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">r</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. Are these two piece</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> of evidence and the corroboration requirement of Scot criminal law is fulfilled, or is it a single piece of evidence that still needs corroborating?</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">3) Due to a known bug in the car’s software, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">a vulnerability</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> is created that allows</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> third parties to hack into a car’s computer system and steal personal information for fraudulent purposes. During a hack, the performance of the other software systems is degraded, and as a result the system reacted </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">too </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">slowly</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The driver</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, relying</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> on his </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">software, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">does not</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> intervene even if he could hav</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">e. An accident follows</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. In the investigation it transpired that the security flaw was known, and that a patch existed, but that the driver had not updated his software for some time.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> The </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">(US based) </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">car manuf</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">acturer automatically updates software for some customers, but </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">o</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">nly if they subscribe to a paid</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">for premium service. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">B) </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">specific </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> legal  issues</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">B.1) schematic overview of the legal issues of autonomous </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">vehicles</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">While this </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">list does not aspire to completeness, it lists the main </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">issues that have come up in discussion so far. As discussed above, they can in varying degrees affect national , international or subnational legal regimes, and are affected in varying ways by the spe</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">cific technology under consideration. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">1)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Road traffic law: </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">a)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Issues  relating to the car itself (Roadworthiness, licensing etc)</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">b)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Issues relating to drivers (Duties of drivers, competent driver)</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">c)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Issues relating to third parties  </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">2)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Delict</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">/tort </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> law and liability</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">3)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Contract law </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">a)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Contracts by manufacturer or  retailer with customer of automated car</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">b)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Contract automatically entered into   by the car</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Criminal law</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">a)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">New forms of crimes “against” the automated car (e.g. hacking of software)</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">b)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">New forms of  crimes committed wit</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">h automated cars</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Evidence and procedure: digital evidence and computer forensics</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">6)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Data protection law</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">7)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Internet and computer law (e.g. Computer Misuse Act)</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">8)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">IP, competition and international trade law</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">a)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ISO standards</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">9)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Environmental and planning law</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">10)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Insurance law</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">11)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Tax law</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">12)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Disability law </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">a)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Linking back to 1: changing definition of competent driver</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">b)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">“digital divide” issues,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> possible </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> right to assistive technology</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">B.2) </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">This section very cursorily and mainly though examples expands on these 11 </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">categories</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">1) Road traffic law. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The UK recently permitted the testing of autonomous vehicles</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> on public roads. This seems to  be an ad hoc permission granted on a case to case basis, which is similar to other such tests in Spain  and Japan.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> The US is already now taki</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ng a more principled approach </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">and some states issue licences for AVs</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> Emerging issues:</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">General rules on testing of the technology with a view on possible</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> future </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">lawful use on public roads – assurances to industry, telling them what they need to prove </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> fairness between competitors/</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">no “hidden state subsidies” </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Revising outdated international regimes such as the 1949 Geneva Convention</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">If AVs become legal to drive on public roads, all relevant legislation will need updating, as recognised in the Action for</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> Roads report by the DoT in 2013. Affected will be in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">particular </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> provisions that refer to relevant mental states such as “reasonable”, “</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">foreseeable</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">” or “intentionally”.  Example from the Road Traffic Act: </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> “</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">If a person drives</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> [...] </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">without due care and at</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">tention, or without reasonable consideration for other persons using the road or place, he is guilty of an offence</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">”</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. The meaning of “attention” might change if the car drives largely autonomously, and other activities presently permitted may become permiss</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ible (e.g. taking a phone call). </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">More generally, h</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ow should the “reasonable consideration” be split between car and driver (and can cars ever said to be “reasonable”? The inverse question also needs </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">addressing -</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> under what conditions should it be prohibite</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">d for a driver to override the computer?</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Important social and regulatory questions concern the skills needed to drive an AV car, which will differ from traditional cars </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Transferability of “old” driver’s licenses?</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Driver licenses for people who in the past</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, due to disability or age, were excluded from the roads</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">? If it can be shown that their risk would not be higher than that of a licensed driver at present in a traditional car, could withholding a license breach their  rights under the Disability Discrimin</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ation Ac</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">t, and possible HR law?</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">With “law compliance by design” emerging as a major approach to regulate information technologies (in particular, “privacy by design”) two important policy issues are raised here</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">- clarification of the law in a way that it b</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ecomes “computational” as soon as possible will facilitate the construction of cars that are “traffic law abiding” by design</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">- this raises however also the issue if, and if so to what degree, cars should be developed that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">can</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> break traffic laws – should we</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> e.g. ever permit a fully autonomous car to ever be able to drive faster than the  speed limit?</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">2) Liability (delict/tort)</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">This area has been the most studied, due to its obvious relevance for industry and car users.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> The main concern is a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> equitable</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> distrib</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ution of risks between manufacturer, retailer, drivers and pedestrians. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Fears that need to be addressed, though not necessarily through legislation, are</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Excessive litigation could destroy the new industry in its infancy</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Insufficient legislation can create</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> inadvertently “liability gaps”, depriving  victims of accidents of redress, or leaving drivers with liability for software faults outside their control. The latter in turn could negatively affect </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">uptake, even if this were only the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> perception of risk. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Insurance regimes will play an important role to manage these concerns, the role of the law here will be mainly to create sufficient predictability to establish rational insurance premiums in a competitive insurance market.  An interesting question here is</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> what should be in</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ured in the future – the driver, the car or the car’s “mind”, the software that it uses. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Should no claims bonuses follow the driver (even though his role is now minimal) or the car that has proven its reliability?</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">3) contracts</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">There are </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">two aspects </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">of</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> contract law in this field. One the one hand, contracts will be used by manufacturers and retailers to manage risks. Issues can arise if risk is shifted unfairly between the parties, raising also potential issues within Europe between jurisd</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ictions t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">h</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">at have sweeping “good faith” </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">tests that</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> can render void contractual agreements, and those that put greater burdens on the buyer. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> Liability and contract regimes for AV cars will evolve synchronously. If for instance producers are held liable for</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> accidents caused by outdated software, they will write the right to “push” software updates automatically on their client’s cars. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The second issue are contracts that the car itself might automatically enter into- paying a road toll, accessing necessary b</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ut paid-for services such as  GPS data, transmitting insurance details to another car after an accident, are a few possible examples. The legal validity of these computer generated contacts is discussed in the general law of robots and automated systems, b</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ut will have a bearing on AVs as well</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4+5) criminal law and criminal procedure</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Undoubtedly, new crimes and security risks will become apparent once the technology is used more widely. The car can in this case become the target (e.g. by hacking into the computer system) or the means of new forms of crime. As with liability issues disc</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ussed above, “omissions “ may play a much greater role than “actions”. Investigating AV crimes will require reliable digital evidence, and with that possible regulations that impose duties to store and collect this evidence in a forensically sound way (for</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> instance in analogy to the “black box” in airplanes). This relates this topic to </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">6+7) Data protection, internet  and computer law</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">AVs will necessitate the collecting and processing of vast amounts of data, both on the car itself and in the infrastructure</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> that supports it. Given how important the cars for many people, the ability to infer highly personal information from this data is ever present. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> Since this affects not just the car, but the entire intelligent infrastructure,” privacy by design” approache</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s are as necessary as data minimisation strategies. It is in this field that the author would see one of the most pressing and urgent needs for action. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Generally, ubiquitous computing poses new privacy challenges that current, internet focussed legislatio</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">n may not adequately address</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. While some of the data will involve transmission via the internet, in particular in cloud based services (whose dangers of privacy have recently become </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">painfully apparent) , other forms of data collection and processing do no</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">t fit the internet paradigm. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">This will also cause particular issues within the EU framework. National data protection regimes , despite the EU framework, differ  significantly, with privacy protection in the UK and Ireland considerably weaker than in many</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> continental systems. With  cars inherently mobile and able to cross national borders, this can become a problem for interoperability, if e.g. German cars were to be prohibited from processing or storing certain data that they may need when driving in the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">UK.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The flipside of DP law are data retention duties and in the UK in particular RIPA, with open legal issues to what extend car manufacturers, retailers or owners become de facto  ISPs or so similar to ISPs that relevant legislation should be extended to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">them .</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">8) </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">IP, competition and international trade law</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">As the example of data protection law above has shown, difference in national laws can result in design choices that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">can </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">impact on the interoperability of cars and road systems. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Traditional cars can dr</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ive on pretty much any road – AV cars may need specific infrastructure to be able to drive. This can raise issues similar to the net neutrality debate- should we require that the infrastructure remains open to all car makers, or would it be permissible tha</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">t say Google cars can only drive on Google maintained roads, or that their cars get at least preferential  treatment on roads where they provide infrastructure? </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The much greater complexity that comes with an AV system will generally increase the danger of</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> fragmented markets and interoperability. Standard setting, especially international standards, will be the obvious regularity means to address this, and will also have to play a significant role in determining liability issues alluded to above. This will </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">inevitably raise legal issues regarding  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">standard-essential patent</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s and licensing. On the one hand, inventors and developers of AV cars need to be rewarded through appropriate IP, on the other, market fragmentation in the transport infrastructure could be </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">particularly socially harmful</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">Literature</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Gasseret Tom M. all BASt-Bericht F 83, Projektgruppe "Rechtsfolgen zunehmender Fahrzeugautomatisierung" 2012</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Graham, Kyle ‘Of Frightened Horses and Autonomous Vehicles: Tort Law and Its Assimilations of Innovations’</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> Vol 52 Santa Clara Law Review (2012).</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Kalra, Nidhi James Anderson and Martin Wachs, ‘Liability and Regulation of Autonomous Vehicle Technologies’ California PATH Research Report (2009) </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Leroux</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, Christophe</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> et al </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Suggestion</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> for a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">green paper</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> on </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">legal issues</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">robotics Report for Deliverable 2.3 of the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">European Robotics Coordination Action 2012</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">LeValley</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Dylan, ‘Autonomous Vehicle Liability – Application of Common Carrier Liability’ Vol 36(5) Seattle University Law Review (2013).</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Schafer,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Burkhard, Wiebke Abel 'The German Constitutional Court on the Right in Confidentiality and Integrity of Information Technology Systems' (2009) </span><a href="http://www.law.ed.ac.uk/ahrc/script-ed/" target="new"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; text-decoration:underline">SCRIPT-</span><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; text-decoration:underline">ed</span></a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> pp106-123 </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Vol</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> 6</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Smith,  Bryant Walker </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">“Automated vehicles are probably legal in the United States, Centre for internet and Society 2012, </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Svarcast</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Francesca, ‘Turning a New Leaf: A Privacy Analysis of Carwings: Electric Vehicle Data Collection and Transmission’ 29 Santa Clara Computer &amp; High T</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">echnology Law Journal 166 (2012). </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">van der Heijden Rob and Kiliaan van Wees, ‘Introducing Advanced Driver Assistance Systems: Some Legal Issues’ Vol 1(3) European Journal of Transport and Infrastructure Research (2001) 309-326.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Pinto</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Cyrus, ‘How Autonomou</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s Vehicle Policy in California and Nevada Addresses Technological and Non-Technological Liabilities’ Vol 5(1) Intersect – Stanford University (2012). </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">November 2013</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>